Left bank: Medoc. Flat, featureless landscape, gravel soil reclaimed from sea, suitable for Cabernet Sauvignon. Mostly large wineries owned by banks, wines with majority of Cabernet Sauvignon, with some Merlot, Cabernet Franc or Petite Bordeaux.

Right bank: hilly, picturesque, Chateu de Pomerol, Saint-Emilion etc. -- primarily Merlot with Cabernet Franc.